# Solution: rust_data_streaming_expert_013_architectural_understanding_expert_01

## Key Files Identified

- /app/project/src/config.txt - Global TOML runtime configuration defining Kafka brokers, pipeline settings, worker pool sizes, quality checks, feature flags, and Iceberg catalog settings
- /app/project/package.json - Project metadata listing key dependencies (kafkajs, node-rdkafka, prom-client) and keywords (kafka, iceberg, etl, sentiment-analysis, stream-processing)
- /app/project/README.md - High-level architecture overview with Mermaid diagram showing pipeline stages: Ingestion → Quality Control → Enrichment Workers → Iceberg Data Lake
- /app/project/docs/api.md - SDK documentation showing FireHose consumer, enrichment Pipeline stages, and strategy pattern for custom algorithms
- /app/project/src/constants.txt - Compile-time constants defining Kafka topic names (`chirp.raw.events`, `chirp.clean.events`, `chirp.enriched.events`), concurrency defaults, and Iceberg warehouse settings
- /app/project/src/module_79.txt - **Quality Control & Enrichment stage** (QC pipeline): validates incoming raw social events, deduplicates, applies quality rules, forwards to sink Kafka topic
- /app/project/src/module_22.txt - **Sentiment analysis stream processor**: consumes `raw_social_stream` from Kafka, enriches with sentiment via Strategy pattern, produces to `enriched_social_stream` — uses `tokio::sync::mpsc` channel for DLQ
- /app/project/src/module_81.txt - **Ingestion + enrichment edge service**: consumes raw events from Kafka, applies configurable transformation pipeline with `Transformer` trait, uses `mpsc::channel` for control signals
- /app/project/src/module_34.txt - **Enrichment & Data-Quality Pipeline** using `tokio::sync::mpsc` channels (`Receiver<SocialEvent>` → `Sender<EnrichedEvent>`) with explicit back-pressure semantics between normalization and enrichment stages
- /app/project/src/module_78.txt - **Real-time enrichment and quality control pipeline** with `run_pipeline()` accepting a `Stream<Item=SocialEvent>` input and `Sender<EnrichedEvent>` output via bounded mpsc channels
- /app/project/src/module_56.txt - **Sentiment engine** with explicit `mpsc::channel::<api::RawEvent>(CHANNEL_CAPACITY)` and `mpsc::channel::<api::EnrichedEvent>(CHANNEL_CAPACITY)` — `CHANNEL_CAPACITY = 16_384` — demonstrating the in-process coupling
- /app/project/src/module_27.txt - **EnrichmentOrchestrator** wiring `mpsc::Receiver<SocialEvent>` input to `mpsc::Sender<EnrichedEvent>` output with `CHANNEL_DEPTH` constant
- /app/project/src/module_63.txt - **Sentiment enricher** with full pipeline diagram: `Kafka In → Quality Check → Sentiment Algo → Kafka Out`
- /app/project/src/module_11.txt - Sentiment enrichment micro-service consuming raw social events and publishing enriched events
- /app/project/src/utils.txt - Shared utilities: retry with exponential backoff, spawn_named_task, partition key hashing, metrics timing

## Code Evidence

